--------------------------------------------------

External systems influence the state:

National Factors:

• federal policies
• national economic cycles
• political tensions

Global Factors:

• economic cycles
• technological waves
• climate pressures
• investment flows


--------------------------------------------------
EVENT SYSTEM
--------------------------------------------------

Events may occur periodically.

Examples:

• flood or drought
• corruption scandal
• investment opportunity
• corporate expansion
• infrastructure failure
• social protest
• technology breakthrough


--------------------------------------------------
REPUTATION SYSTEM
--------------------------------------------------

The state develops a reputation over time.

Possible reputations:

• investment magnet
• corrupt administration
• innovation powerhouse
• unstable politics
• green development leader
• industrial powerhouse

Reputation affects investment and migration.


